WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:02.500 --> 00:00:04.033
The whitening products on the market

00:00:04.033 --> 00:00:05.266
are divided into two categories.

00:00:05.300 --> 00:00:07.100
One is a single-point attack.

00:00:07.100 --> 00:00:09.100
For example, because I inhibited the production

00:00:09.100 --> 00:00:10.233
, we can whiten the skin.

00:00:10.233 --> 00:00:11.400
Because I inhibited the transport

00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:12.333
, we can whiten

00:00:12.333 --> 00:00:14.700
the skin . The other is an indiscriminate attack.

00:00:14.700 --> 00:00:17.200
I have matched all the ingredients in all the steps

00:00:17.200 --> 00:00:19.033
, but the amount of each one is insufficient.

00:00:19.133 --> 00:00:21.133
So, for these two types of whitening products,

00:00:21.133 --> 00:00:22.133
if the step targeted by the

00:00:22.133 --> 00:00:24.733
former

00:00:24.733 --> 00:00:27.233
does not match your skin type,

00:00:27.233 --> 00:00:28.600
you will not get white after using it.

00:00:28.666 --> 00:00:30.000
And for the latter, no matter

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:31.800
how you use it, the effect

00:00:31.800 --> 00:00:32.866
is unsatisfactory.

00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:35.666
So, before I introduce our product selection to you, there

00:00:35.666 --> 00:00:37.066
is another very important point

00:00:37.066 --> 00:00:39.666
, that is, we need to first determine

00:00:39.666 --> 00:00:41.666
what our skin type is.

00:00:41.733 --> 00:00:44.300
Because even if the ingredients are used correctly,

00:00:44.333 --> 00:00:46.233
but the skin type is not matched,

00:00:46.233 --> 00:00:47.866
the product is still useless

00:00:47.866 --> 00:00:49.400
and may cause allergies

00:00:49.533 --> 00:00:50.733
. So

00:00:50.733 --> 00:00:51.866
how do we define skin types?

00:00:51.866 --> 00:00:54.000
There are some statistical definitions of this in academia

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.266
, but we can't spend 100,000 yuan

00:00:56.266 --> 00:00:58.100
to bring a detector home

00:00:58.100 --> 00:00:59.400
to identify skin type

00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:00.100
, so here

00:01:00.100 --> 00:01:02.300
I will teach you a relatively simple

00:01:02.300 --> 00:01:03.833
method to identify skin type.

00:01:04.133 --> 00:01:05.400
The method is as follows:

00:01:05.400 --> 00:01:07.700
First, prepare a piece of oil-absorbing paper.

00:01:07.700 --> 00:01:09.300
Then, wash your face

00:01:09.300 --> 00:01:11.800
. After washing it, do not use any skin care procedures

00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:13.200
or products.

00:01:13.200 --> 00:01:14.466
Sit quietly

00:01:14.466 --> 00:01:15.866
in a constant temperature place

00:01:15.866 --> 00:01:18.100
in the room for one to two hours

00:01:18.233 --> 00:01:19.500
. After one to two hours,

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:22.200
use this oil-absorbing paper to absorb the oil on your face.

00:01:22.300 --> 00:01:24.600
If there is oil everywhere you touch,

00:01:24.600 --> 00:01:25.866
you have oily skin.

00:01:25.900 --> 00:01:28.100
If there is no oil anywhere,

00:01:28.100 --> 00:01:29.533
you have dry skin.

00:01:29.633 --> 00:01:31.466
If there is oil in your T-zone

00:01:31.466 --> 00:01:33.133
and no oil on your cheeks

00:01:33.133 --> 00:01:35.033
, but your cheeks don't feel tight,

00:01:35.033 --> 00:01:36.800
you have combination skin.

00:01:36.933 --> 00:01:38.333
If there is oil in your T-zone

00:01:38.333 --> 00:01:41.066
but your cheeks feel tight and uncomfortable,

00:01:41.200 --> 00:01:43.033
you have combination skin. For dry skin,

00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:45.333
we can roughly divide skin into these

00:01:45.333 --> 00:01:47.066
four types.

00:01:47.333 --> 00:01:49.466
The four skin types we just mentioned

00:01:49.466 --> 00:01:53.066
are combined with the four darkening constitutions mentioned at the beginning.

00:01:53.066 --> 00:01:54.400
Pulling the table horizontally and vertically

00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:56.400
will form a 16-square grid

00:01:56.400 --> 00:01:59.233
, which is our 16-type whitening method.

00:01:59.233 --> 00:02:01.433
As long as you find your own skin type

00:02:01.433 --> 00:02:04.000
and what your darkening constitution is,

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:07.100
you will find a whitening method that suits you.

00:02:14.200 --> 00:02:17.200
OK, now we enter the most practical part

00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:19.000
, which is how to choose products

00:02:19.200 --> 00:02:21.633
. Let's explain them one by one according to the darkening type.

00:02:21.666 --> 00:02:23.100
The first type is the tanning type .

00:02:23.133 --> 00:02:23.733
I just said that

00:02:23.733 --> 00:02:26.200
the tanning type has two ingredients that are particularly suitable,

00:02:26.200 --> 00:02:27.233
